sequenceDiagram
    participant U as 👤 User (Browser)
    participant W as 🌐 Web App
    participant G as 🚀 Gateway
    participant C as 🤖 Claude API
    participant T as 🔧 Tool (Jira)
    participant DB as 💾 Database

    U->>W: Open ai.zivtech.com
    W->>G: Check session
    G->>DB: Validate session
    DB-->>G: User authenticated
    G-->>W: Session valid
    W-->>U: Show chat interface

    U->>W: "What are my Jira tickets?"
    W->>G: POST /api/v1/chat
    G->>DB: Create message

    G->>C: messages.create (streaming)

    Note over G,C: Claude decides to use tool

    C-->>G: tool_use: jira_get_my_issues
    G-->>W: SSE: tool_call event
    W-->>U: Show "Using Jira..."

    G->>T: Execute jira_get_my_issues
    T->>DB: Get user's Jira token
    DB-->>T: Encrypted token
    T->>T: Decrypt token
    T-->>G: [5 tickets]

    G-->>W: SSE: tool_result event
    W-->>U: Show ticket preview

    G->>C: Continue with tool result

    loop Streaming Response
        C-->>G: text delta
        G-->>W: SSE: token event
        W-->>U: Append to message
    end

    C-->>G: message_stop
    G->>DB: Save assistant message
    G->>DB: Log tool execution
    G-->>W: SSE: complete event
    W-->>U: Show final message + feedback buttons
